The paper focuses on a framework for improving data quality through user feedback and machine learning techniques. This involves repairing the database and refining the training set for the model. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves active learning and decision-theory concepts, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
